00444 void ZNtupleDumper::analyze(const edm::Event& iEvent, const edm::EventSetup& iSetup)
00445 {
00446   //  using namespace edm;
00447  
00448   pEvent = &iEvent;
00449   pSetup = &iSetup;
00450   
00451   // filling infos runNumber, eventNumber, lumi
00452   if( !iEvent.isRealData() ){
00453     iEvent.getByLabel(edm::InputTag("addPileupInfo"), PupInfo);
00454     iEvent.getByLabel(edm::InputTag("generator"), GenEventInfoHandle);
00455     isMC=true;
00456   } else isMC=false;
00457   
00458   //------------------------------ CONVERSIONS
00459   iEvent.getByLabel(conversionsProducerTAG, conversionsHandle);
00460 
00461   //------------------------------ HLT
00462   iEvent.getByLabel(triggerResultsTAG, triggerResultsHandle);
00463 
00464   //------------------------------
00465   clustertools = new EcalClusterLazyTools (iEvent, iSetup, recHitCollectionEBTAG, 
00466                                            recHitCollectionEETAG);  
00467 
00468   //------------------------------ electrons
00469   iEvent.getByLabel(electronsTAG, electronsHandle);
00470 
00471   // for conversions with full vertex fit
00472   //------------------------------  VERTEX
00473   iEvent.getByLabel(vtxCollectionTAG, primaryVertexHandle); 
00474   iEvent.getByLabel(BeamSpotTAG, bsHandle);
00475   iEvent.getByLabel(rhoTAG,rhoHandle);
00476   
00477   iEvent.getByLabel(metTAG, metHandle); 
00478   //if(metHandle.isValid()==false) iEvent.getByType(metHandle);
00479   reco::PFMET met = ((*metHandle))[0]; 
00480 
00481   TreeSetEventSummaryVar(iEvent);
00482   TreeSetPileupVar(); // this can be filled once per event
00483   
00484   // at least one of the triggers
00485   HLTfire=false;
00486   if(!hltPaths.empty()){
00487     for(std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator hltPath_itr = hltPaths.begin();
00488         hltPath_itr != hltPaths.end();
00489         hltPath_itr++){
00490       if(hltPath_itr->empty()) continue;
00491       std::map<std::string, bool>::const_iterator it = HLTBits.find(*hltPath_itr);
00492       if(it!=HLTBits.end()){
00493         HLTfire+=it->second;
00494         //      std::cout << "Not empty:" << hltPaths[0] << "\t" << it->first << "\t" << it->second << "\t" << triggerFire << std::endl;
00495         //}else{
00496 //      for(std::map<std::string, bool>::const_iterator it_ = HLTBits.begin();
00497 //          it_!=HLTBits.end();
00498 //          it_++){
00499 //        std::cout  << "\t" << it_->first << "\t" << it_->second << std::endl;
00500 //      }
00501 //      edm::LogError("ZNtupleDumper") << "HLT path required but not find in TriggerResults" << " " << HLTBits.size();
00502         //edm::LogWarning("ZNtupleDumper") << "HLT path " << *hltPath_itr << " required but not found in TriggerResults" << " " << HLTBits.size();
00503         //exit(1);
00504       }
00505     }
00506   } 
00507 
00508   // count electrons
00509   int nWP70 = 0; //only WP70
00510   int nWP90 = 0; //only WP90
00511   for( pat::ElectronCollection::const_iterator eleIter1 = electronsHandle->begin();
00512        eleIter1 != electronsHandle->end();
00513        eleIter1++){
00514     if( eleIter1->electronID("tight") )
00515       {
00516         ++nWP70;
00517         continue;
00518       }
00519     if( eleIter1->electronID("loose") )
00520       {

00561         if(mass < 55 || mass > 125) continue;
00562       
00563         //       ZCandidatesCollection.push_back(zeeCandidate);
00564         TreeSetDiElectronVar(*eleIter1, *eleIter2);

00570         if(doEleIDTree){
